data.description:
Welcome to 5431 EverLook Circle in Evans, Georgia, located in the highly sought-after Crawford Creek subdivision. This stunning home offers four bedrooms and 3 1/2 baths, spanning over 2900 square feet of elegant living space. 

One of the standout features of this home is the owner's suite, conveniently located on the main level, providing a private retreat for homeowners. The remaining three bedrooms are spacious and offer ample closet space for all your storage needs.

The backyard of this property is truly a gem, offering plenty of space for outdoor activities and relaxation. Whether you envision hosting gatherings or simply enjoying some quiet time outdoors, this backyard will cater to your every need.

Living in the Crawford Creek subdivision comes with its own set of perks. Residents have access to a variety of amenities, including a swimming pool, basketball goal area, and walking trails. Additionally, there is a covered pavilion with a fire pit, perfect for cozy evenings with friends and family.

The location of this home is ideal for those seeking convenience. With its proximity to Fort Eisenhower, shopping centers, restaurants, and parks, everything you need is just a short distance away. Not to mention, the area is known for its great schools, making it an ideal choice for families.

Don't miss the opportunity to make this beautiful home yours. Schedule a showing today and experience the best of Evans, Georgia living at 5431 EverLook Circle.
